gsang>SingSang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1491<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(3/14/03 5:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1136.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://66.93.39.18/images/Singthumb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who wants raid leader training assistance?</span><hr size=1> Often, I have something going on either Monday <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>or</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Tuesday, but usually not both. For example, I have Kael this Monday. If we wind up doing plate cycle, then I can skip that a little easier than the arena (Plate cycle is predicable and crowd control is handled much differently than Arena). If it's areana (which won't be known until raid time), then my presence is likely to be missed a bit more due to crowd control concerns. There is some possibility that there will be an Ixxy kill Tuesday, but they will probably do that before I'm even on, and I wouldn't be missed for that one regardless. So, for this week, Tuesday would probably be best for me if we can do something on that short of notice.<br>
<br>
It would be great if we could do two groups since this is raid training, but we could mock things up otherwise. I would say that this could be a 35-53 thing if folks want XP, and perhaps 30-65 if folks are willing to bypass the xp thing in favor of just the tactics and loot thing (there is a limit to how many 30's we can stand). A chanter is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>highly</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> desirable.<br>
<br>
Anyone who does not have a Howling Stones (aka Charrasis) key should think about trying to attend this. I would suggest that looting be highest level that doesn't have a Xalgozian Fang already (half the needed quest itmes). Xalgoz drops one or two Xalgozian Fangs when he spawns, has PH's, and is on a 30 minute timer. I'd suggest that we plan on two hours (5 Xalgoz or PH kills) from when we get to the church.<br>
<br>
If there is time afterward, we can go see if the Chancellor is up and get someone the Jade prod they need to complete the quest - it is also purchasable in the bazaar.<br>
<br>
Info on the key to charrasis quest below:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><br>
 If you hail a Froglok named Dugroz in the Swamp of No Hope he will engage you in a discussion which ultimately leads to the award of keys to Charasis (Howling Stones). Dugroz is located slightly Southwest of the zone to Trakanon's Teeth near the entrance to the Frog City in the Swamp of No Hope. He should be indifferent to all races and classes so it is difficult to say whether or not he sees through invisibility (in the rare case that someone is KOS). He asks you to bring him two items, the Fang of Xalgoz and a Jade Chokidai Prod in return for this key.<br>
<br>
Deep in the bowels of the Ruins of Kaesora, there is a church where the demon Xalgoz spawns. His spawn location is on a 30 minute timer and seems to spawn himself or a PH at a 50/50 ratio. He drops the Fang of Xalgoz (sometimes twice) as well as a few other decent drops.<br>
Note: these fangs are NO DROP.<br>
<br>
At the back of the sarnak fortress in the Lake of Ill Omen, there is a named sarnak: Chancellor who drops the Jade Chokidai Prod. He spawns on a 2 hour timer (to the minute) and drops the prod 90% of the time.<br>
<br>
Return both items to Dugroz and he will reward you with a key to Charasis (Howling Stones).<br>
Note: These items can be multiquested, and the prod is not NO DROP.<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Checklist<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :unchecked --><img src=http://www.exodusfellowship.com/uncheckedbox.gif ALT=":unchecked"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Fang of Xalgoz<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :unchecked --><img src=http://www.exodusfellowship.com/uncheckedbox.gif ALT=":unchecked"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Jade Chokidai Prod<br>
<br>
It worth noting that I had to kill the Chancellor 3 times to get my prod. /sigh. I could solo him at 49, though most classes say no until around 55 or so. I know it took a couple of botched runs (thankfully not ending in death) for me to learn a strategy that would work for me (I charm him, use him to clear the room, and then just finish him by kiting him around the room). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Mebigghoo</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#A8A8A8>(3/15/03 3:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1136.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I need training</span><hr size=1> I need training<br>
